To compile maskverif, the best way is to use nix:
> nix-shell
> make

Then you can start using it iteractively by doing
> ./maskverif
or by passing a .mv file
> ./maskverif < tutorial.mv

A small tutorial is provided in 'tutorial.mv'.



To install maskverif as a library for ocamlfind use:
> sudo apt-get install libgmp-dev m4
> opam install zarith ocamlbuild menhir ocamlgraph batteries
> make library

To install maskverif as executable in your path without opam use:
> make install

Remeber to run "eval $(opam env)", to update your path according.

To remove the executable, including libraries run:
> make uninstall
